<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Moq." family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. paniculata var. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="variety" species="paniculata" variety="scabrida">M. paniculata Moq. var. scabrida</taxonomicName>
(Urb.) Kuntze, Revis. Gen. Pl. 3(3): 268 (1898). Lectotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): BRAZIL. [Without exact location and date] F. Sellow s.n. (F0BN005735, image!). Note: The lectotype is chosen according to the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Urban, I" journalOrPublisher="Jahrbuch des Koeniglichen botanischen Gartens und des botanischen Museums zu Berlin" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="B57" refString="Urban, I, 1885. Ueber den Bluethenbau der Phytolaccaceen-Gattung Microtea. Berichte der Deutschen Botanischen Gesellschaft 3: 324-332." title="Ueber den Bluethenbau der Phytolaccaceen-Gattung Microtea. Berichte der Deutschen Botanischen Gesellschaft 3: 324 - 332." year="1885">Urban 1885</bibRefCitation>
). 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Urban’s">Urban's</normalizedToken>
collections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
in B have probably been missing since 1945.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. paniculata var. latifolia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="variety" species="paniculata" variety="latifolia">M. paniculata var. latifolia</taxonomicName>
Kuntze, Revis. Gen. Pl. 3(3): 268 (1898). Lectotype (Sennikov &amp; Sukhorukov, designated here): BOLIVIA. Rio Yapacani, June 1892, O. Kuntze s.n. (B!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="23" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. foliosa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="foliosa">M. foliosa</taxonomicName>
Chodat, Bull. Herb. Boissier, ser. 2, 3: 418 (1903). Lectotype (designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" author="Nowicke, WH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="294 - 364" refId="B37" refString="Nowicke, WH, 1968. Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 55 (3): 294 - 364, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" title="Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" volume="55" year="1968">Nowicke 1968</bibRefCitation>
: 351): PARAGUAY. In regione collium &quot;Cerros de Tobaty&quot;, September 1900, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">E. Hassler 6254</emphasis>
(MO216419, image! isolectotypes - P00743942! K000601209!). Note: This species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. paniculata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="paniculata">M. paniculata</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. celosioides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="celosioides">M. celosioides</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marchioretto, MS" journalOrPublisher="Pesquisas Botanica" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" pagination="5 - 51" refId="B31" refString="Marchioretto, MS, de Siqueira, JC, 1998. O genero Microtea Sw. (Phytolaccaceae) no Brasil. Pesquisas Botanica 48: 5 - 51" title="O genero Microtea Sw. (Phytolaccaceae) no Brasil." volume="48" year="1998">Marchioretto and de Siqueira (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. We have seen the original specimens cited in the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Chodat, RH" journalOrPublisher="Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="B12" refString="Chodat, RH, Hassler, E, 1903. Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387-421." title="Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387 - 421." year="1903">Chodat and Hassler 1903</bibRefCitation>
): the specimens with the numbers 6254 (MO216419 - image! K000601209! P00743942!), 1649 (P03321197), 1988 (P00743946!) and 1988b (B! P00743944!) are 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
, and the specimens with the number 7605 (K000601208! P00743941!) belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chodat, Bull. Herb. Boissier, ser. 2, 3: 419" authorityYear="1903" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sulcicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="species" species="sulcicaulis">M. sulcicaulis</taxonomicName>
, a species described in the same article by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chodat, RH" journalOrPublisher="Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="B12" refString="Chodat, RH, Hassler, E, 1903. Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387-421." title="Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387 - 421." year="1903">Chodat and Hassler (1903)</bibRefCitation>
. The authors mentioned in the publication three 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Microteaceae" genus="Microtea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microtea" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Microtea</taxonomicName>
species: 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. foliosa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<pageBreakToken pageId="22" pageNumber="23" start="start">M</pageBreakToken>
. foliosa
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. paniculata" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="paniculata">M. paniculata</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chodat, Bull. Herb. Boissier, ser. 2, 3: 419" authorityYear="1903" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sulcicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sulcicaulis">M. sulcicaulis</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chodat, RH" journalOrPublisher="Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="B12" refString="Chodat, RH, Hassler, E, 1903. Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387-421." title="Plantae Hasslerianae - Soit enumeration des plantes recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr. Emile Hassler, d'Aarau (Suisse) de 1885 a 1902. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2 3: 387 - 421." year="1903">Chodat and Hassler 1903</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
was omitted in the species list. The protologue of 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. foliosa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="foliosa">M. foliosa</taxonomicName>
combines the characters of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chodat, Bull. Herb. Boissier, ser. 2, 3: 419" authorityYear="1903" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. sulcicaulis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="sulcicaulis">M. sulcicaulis</taxonomicName>
, but the epithet 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“foliosa”">&quot;foliosa&quot;</normalizedToken>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
with inflorescence leafy in its lower part. Based on the typification made by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" author="Nowicke, WH" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="294 - 364" refId="B37" refString="Nowicke, WH, 1968. Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 55 (3): 294 - 364, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" title="Palynotaxonomic study of the Phytolaccaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2395128" volume="55" year="1968">Nowicke (1968)</bibRefCitation>
, and in agreement with 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter, H" journalOrPublisher="Pflanzengeschichte und Pflanzengeographie (Beiblatt)" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" refId="B61" refString="Walter, H, 1909. Phytolaccaceae. In: Engler A (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, Heft 39. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig." title="Phytolaccaceae. In: Engler A (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich, Heft 39. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig." year="1909">Walter (1909)</bibRefCitation>
, we synonymize 
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. foliosa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="foliosa">M. foliosa</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Urb., Ber. Deutsch. Bot. Ges. 3: 325" authorityYear="1885" family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabrida" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="scabrida">M. scabrida</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName family="Microteaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scandens" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" rank="species" species="scandens">M. scandens</taxonomicName>
Rusby, Mem. New York Bot. Gard. 7: 239 (1927). Holotype: BOLIVIA. La Paz, Iturralde, Ixiamas, alt. 244 m, 18 Dec 1921, 
